## Field Nodes

```
id:               systems_theory
name:             Systems Theory
domain: systems_cybernetics
decade: 1940s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Open systems, feedback loops, homeostasis, equifinality
period_active: 1940s–present
prominence: dominant
tags: foundational, interdisciplinary
notes:            Originated with von Bertalanffy's general systems theory; pervasive influence across all complexity streams
```

```
id:               cybernetics
name:             Cybernetics
domain: systems_cybernetics
decade: 1940s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Feedback, control, communication, circular causality
period_active: 1940s–1970s
prominence: dominant
tags: foundational, information
notes:            Wiener, Ashby, McCulloch — the science of communication and control in animals and machines
```

```
id:               artificial_intelligence
name:             Artificial Intelligence
domain: ai_cognitive
decade: 1960s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Symbol manipulation, search, neural networks, machine learning
period_active: 1956–present
prominence: dominant
tags: computation, cognition
notes:            Dartmouth conference 1956; alternating winters and springs; now converging with complexity
```

```
id:               cognitive_science
name:             Cognitive Science
domain: ai_cognitive
decade: 1960s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Mental representations, connectionism, embodied cognition, situated cognition
period_active: 1960s–present
prominence: major
tags: cognition, interdisciplinary
notes:            Bridging AI, psychology, linguistics, philosophy, neuroscience
```

```
id:               mathematical_complexity
name:             Mathematical Complexity
domain: math_physical
decade: 1940s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Computational complexity, algorithmic information, Turing machines, Kolmogorov complexity
period_active: 1940s–present
prominence: major
tags: formal, foundational
notes:            Formal foundations underpinning all complexity science; Turing, Gödel, Kolmogorov
```

```
id:               catastrophe_theory
name:             Catastrophe Theory
domain: math_physical
decade: 1970s
field_type: bridging
key_concepts: Bifurcation, topological discontinuity, fold catastrophe
period_active: 1968–1980s
prominence: minor
tags: mathematics, dynamics
notes:            René Thom; brief intense interest then criticism, but ideas absorbed into dynamical systems
```

```
id:               complex_systems
name:             Complex Systems
domain: core_complexity
decade: 1970s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Nonlinearity, feedback, adaptation, path dependence
period_active: 1970s–present
prominence: dominant
tags: foundational, core
notes:            Umbrella field encompassing many sub-disciplines; Santa Fe Institute as institutional anchor
```

```
id:               self_organization
name:             Self-Organization
domain: core_complexity
decade: 1970s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Spontaneous order, dissipative structures, pattern formation, autopoiesis
period_active: 1960s–present
prominence: major
tags: core, dynamics
notes:            Prigogine's dissipative structures; Haken's synergetics; Maturana & Varela's autopoiesis
```

```
id:               complex_adaptive_systems
name:             Complex Adaptive Systems
domain: core_complexity
decade: 1980s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Adaptation, fitness landscapes, co-evolution, schemas, building blocks
period_active: 1980s–present
prominence: dominant
tags: core, santa_fe
notes:            Holland, Kauffman, Gell-Mann at the Santa Fe Institute; agents adapting to each other
```

```
id:               emergence
name:             Emergence
domain: emergence_dynamics
decade: 1980s
field_type: bridging
key_concepts: Macro from micro, downward causation, strong vs weak emergence, levels
period_active: 1980s–present
prominence: dominant
tags: core, philosophical
notes:            Central bridging concept connecting dynamics, computation, and philosophy of complexity
```

```
id:               systems_dynamics
name:             Systems Dynamics
domain: emergence_dynamics
decade: 1960s
field_type: applied
key_concepts: Stock-flow diagrams, feedback loops, simulation, limits to growth
period_active: 1960s–present
prominence: major
tags: modelling, policy
notes:            Jay Forrester at MIT; Club of Rome; Donella Meadows; World3 model
```

```
id:               chaos_theory
name:             Chaos Theory
domain: math_physical
decade: 1970s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Sensitive dependence, strange attractors, Lorenz attractor, period doubling
period_active: 1963–present
prominence: major
tags: dynamics, nonlinear
notes:            Lorenz (1963), May (1976), Feigenbaum universality; popularized by Gleick (1987)
```

```
id:               fractal_geometry
name:             Fractal Geometry
domain: math_physical
decade: 1980s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Self-similarity, fractal dimension, power laws, scale invariance
period_active: 1975–present
prominence: major
tags: mathematics, geometry
notes:            Mandelbrot's fractal geometry of nature; ubiquitous scaling in complex systems
```

```
id:               network_science
name:             Network Science
domain: networks_computation
decade: 1990s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Small-world networks, scale-free topology, hubs, preferential attachment, community structure
period_active: 1998–present
prominence: dominant
tags: core, computational
notes:            Watts & Strogatz (1998), Barabási & Albert (1999); transformed understanding of complex structure
```

```
id:               computational_complexity
name:             Computational Complexity
domain: networks_computation
decade: 2000s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: P vs NP, cellular automata, computational irreducibility, Wolfram
period_active: 1970s–present
prominence: major
tags: computation, formal
notes:            Computational perspective on complexity; Wolfram's New Kind of Science (2002)
```

```
id:               spatial_complexity
name:             Spatial Complexity
domain: networks_computation
decade: 2010s
field_type: applied
key_concepts: GIS, spatial networks, urban scaling, geographic complexity
period_active: 2000s–present
prominence: major
tags: applied, spatial
notes:            Complexity meets geography; urban science, spatial epidemiology
```

```
id:               social_network_theory
name:             Social Network Theory
domain: social_economic
decade: 1970s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Weak ties, structural holes, social capital, embeddedness
period_active: 1970s–present
prominence: major
tags: social, networks
notes:            Granovetter, Burt, Lin; sociological foundation for network science
```

```
id:               economic_financial_complexity
name:             Economic & Financial Complexity
domain: social_economic
decade: 1990s
field_type: applied
key_concepts: Agent-based economics, market microstructure, economic fitness, wealth distribution
period_active: 1990s–present
prominence: major
tags: economics, finance
notes:            Santa Fe Artificial Stock Market; Brian Arthur's increasing returns; econophysics
```

```
id:               big_data
name:             BIG DATA / Data Science
domain: social_economic
decade: 2000s
field_type: emerging
key_concepts: Machine learning, computational social science, digital traces, prediction
period_active: 2005–present
prominence: major
tags: data, computational
notes:            Massive datasets enabling new complexity research; social physics; Pentland, Lazer
```

```
id:               physics_complex_systems
name:             Physics of Complex Systems
domain: math_physical
decade: 1980s
field_type: foundational
key_concepts: Phase transitions, critical phenomena, spin glasses, statistical mechanics of complexity
period_active: 1970s–present
prominence: major
tags: physics, statistical
notes:            Anderson's "More is Different"; spin glasses; renormalization group applied to complexity
```

```
id:               applied_complexity
name:             Applied Complexity
domain: networks_computation
decade: 2010s
field_type: applied
key_concepts: Policy modelling, health systems, organizational complexity, resilience
period_active: 2000s–present
prominence: major
tags: applied, interdisciplinary
notes:            Complexity science reaching policy, public health, management, military planning
```

```
id:               agent_based_modelling
name:             Agent-Based Modelling
domain: emergence_dynamics
decade: 1990s
field_type: bridging
key_concepts: Bottom-up simulation, heterogeneous agents, emergence from rules, computational experiments
period_active: 1990s–present
prominence: major
tags: modelling, simulation
notes:            Epstein & Axtell's Sugarscape; Schelling segregation model; computational laboratory for emergence
```

